floods. \u201cThe sadness of losing the crop [to floods] doesn\u2019t go away until there is another good produce. But the floods keep taking our crops away,\u201d says Chaitanya. \u201cThis stress is further compounded by the worry of defaulting on loans.\u201d According to Maharashtra government\u2019s Department of Agriculture, natural disasters affected 24.68 lakh hectares of land in the state between July and October 2022; just for the month of October, those figures were at 7.5 lakh hectares of land affected in 22 districts. The state received 1,288 mm of rain until October 28, 2022 \u2013 120.5 per cent of the average rainfall. And 1,068 mm of it was received between June and October. [Also read: When it rains, it pours misery ] <img alt=\"The July 2021 floods caused massive destruction to crops in Arjunwad, including these banana trees whose fruits were on the verge on being harvested\" class=\"lazyload\" data-src=\"/media/images/09a-IMG_7615-SJ.max-1400x1120.jpg\" src=\"/media/images/09a-IMG_7615-SJ.height-560.jpg\" style=\" height:390px;\"/>", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "bf0b2d80-5726-4641-9802-cfcd92060009": {"__data__": {"id_": "bf0b2d80-5726-4641-9802-cfcd92060009", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://ruralindiaonline.org/en/articles/we-are-drowning-in-the-fear-of-floods/", "Author": "\n\n\n\n\nSanket Jain\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n", "Publisher": "People's Archive of Rural India", "Type": "Web"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "\u2018We are drowning in the fear of floods\u2019", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://ruralindiaonline.org/en/articles/we-are-drowning-in-the-fear-of-floods/", "Author": "\n\n\n\n\nSanket Jain\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n", "Publisher": "People's Archive of Rural India", "Type": "Web"}, "